Moroccan spice blend in a dry pan toast
cinnamon cloves coriander fenugreek and

cumin when the seeds start to pop
they're ready add paprika and grind into
a fine powder for the hummus peel and
chop butternut squash put on a baking

chopped ginger
drizzle with olive oil seasoned and
sprinkle over the spice mix
then roast in a hot oven for half an
hour inches soft allowed to cool and
place in a blender
at tahini a nutty pace made from sesame
seeds cooked chickpeas a dash of lemon

Flitz into a luxurious and creamy and
